#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:4
msgid "Panels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:6
msgid ""
"Panels are collapsible sections within regions to help organize the "
"interface. They are used in the *Properties Editor*, but also for example"
" in the *Tool Shelf* and the *Properties region*. Some panels are only "
"shown depending on the editors mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:13
msgid "Collapsing and expanding"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:15
msgid ""
"A triangle on the left of the title shows the expanded (▼) and collapsed "
"(►) state of the panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:20
msgid "Panels in expanded and collapsed state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:22
msgid ""
"Expanded (1) and collapsed (2) Panels in the Properties Editor (right "
"area) and in the additional Regions of the 3D View Editor (left area)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:25
msgid ""
"A click with the :kbd:`LMB` on the title area of a panel expands or "
"collapses it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:26
msgid ""
"A :kbd:`LMB` drag motion over the title area will expand or collapse many"
" at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:27
msgid ""
"A :kbd:`Ctrl-LMB` click on the title area of a specific panel will "
"collapse all other panels and make this the only expanded one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:32
msgid "Position"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:34
msgid ""
"You can change the position of a panel within its region by clicking and "
"dragging it with the :kbd:`LMB` on the little widget (\\:\\:\\:\\:) in "
"the upper right corner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:39
msgid "Zoom"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:41
msgid ""
"The zoom factor of a whole region with panels can be changed by :kbd"
":`Ctrl-MMB` clicking and moving the mouse anywhere within that region or "
"use the :kbd:`NumpadPlus` and :kbd:`NumpadMinus` to zoom in and out the "
"contents. Pressing :kbd:`Home` (Show All) will reset the zooming at the "
"screen/panel focused by the mouse pointer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:48
msgid "Alignment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/panels.rst:50
msgid ""
"The alignment of the panels in the *Properties Editor* can be changed "
"between vertical and horizontal. To do this click with :kbd:`RMB` "
"somewhere within the main region of the *Properties Editor* and choose "
"either *Horizontal* or *Vertical* from the appearing menu. Keep in mind "
"though that the panels are optimized for vertical alignment."
msgstr ""

